==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Keystone
<hw>Key"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>The central or topmost stone of an arch. This in some styles is
made different in size from the other voussoirs, or projects, or is
decorated with carving. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Arch</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keystone State</ent>⟦br⟧
